In data framework, we don't see any code in terms of DSDS(e.g. switch data connection from SIM1 to SIM2). For instance, in MTK architecture, we have a DcSwitchManager, DcSwitchAsyncChannel, DcSwitchSate to do this kinda of things.
In Qualcomm's architecture, seems the switching stuff might be putted in RILD, but that would cause large porting effort for customer if they use different modem.
Therefore we highly recommended that Qualcomm would reference MTK's architecture. Thanks.

